1
00:00:02,627 --> 00:00:04,261
♪

2
00:00:05,964 --> 00:00:07,965
♪

3
00:01:07,293 --> 00:01:09,293
♪

4
00:01:56,458 --> 00:01:57,791
[IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]

5
00:02:11,974 --> 00:02:14,424
[IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]

6
00:02:19,982 --> 00:02:24,768
[MUFFLED EXPLOSION]

7
00:02:27,756 --> 00:02:29,589
[IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]

8
00:02:45,307 --> 00:02:47,107
[SCREAMING & SHOUTING]

9
00:03:06,111 --> 00:03:07,111
[GROWLS]

10
00:03:31,904 --> 00:03:33,798
You've done well, son.

11
00:03:33,822 --> 00:03:35,755
Thank you, Father.

12
00:03:37,292 --> 00:03:38,653
As you say,

13
00:03:38,677 --> 00:03:43,975
it is our destiny to bring peace and order to the universe.

14
00:03:43,999 --> 00:03:47,161
I chose wisely when I adopted you, Kal-El.

15
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:50,431
You have honored me where others failed.

16
00:03:50,455 --> 00:03:52,517
As a reward for today's conquest,

17
00:03:52,541 --> 00:03:54,936
I'm giving you your own world to rule.

18
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,920
[LAUGHING]

19
00:03:55,944 --> 00:03:57,788
All hail King Kal!

20
00:03:57,812 --> 00:03:59,190
Way to go, big guy.

21
00:03:59,214 --> 00:04:01,643
This calls for a celebration.

22
00:04:01,667 --> 00:04:02,661
DARKSEID: Go on.

23
00:04:02,685 --> 00:04:05,229
Savor the fruits of your victory, Kal.

24
00:04:05,253 --> 00:04:06,665
You've earned it.

25
00:04:06,689 --> 00:04:07,932
[ALL CHEERING]

26
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:10,502
Oh, yeah! LASHINA: This is gonna be fun.

27
00:04:10,526 --> 00:04:12,337
By the way, Father,

28
00:04:12,361 --> 00:04:14,172
which planet will be mine?

29
00:04:14,196 --> 00:04:16,541
A wealthy but untamed world.

30
00:04:16,565 --> 00:04:19,678
Bringing it under your heel will be your greatest triumph.

31
00:04:19,702 --> 00:04:22,168
It is called Earth.

32
00:04:23,322 --> 00:04:25,322
♪

33
00:04:30,762 --> 00:04:31,723
BOY: Look!

34
00:04:31,747 --> 00:04:32,890
It's Superman!

35
00:04:32,914 --> 00:04:35,082
There's something you don't see in Kansas.

36
00:04:39,420 --> 00:04:40,815
Earth to Clark.

37
00:04:40,839 --> 00:04:43,606
Hello? Anyone home?

38
00:04:45,443 --> 00:04:46,487
[SNAPS]

39
00:04:46,511 --> 00:04:48,406
Huh? Oh, sorry, Lois...

40
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:49,991
guess my mind must've been

41
00:04:50,015 --> 00:04:51,392
somewhere else.

42
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:53,895
<i>Well, snap out of it, Smallville, I'm starving.</i>

43
00:04:53,919 --> 00:04:55,330
<i>Two, please.</i>

44
00:04:55,354 --> 00:04:57,286
[BEEPING]

45
00:04:58,357 --> 00:05:00,001
<i>Superman Central.</i>

46
00:05:00,025 --> 00:05:01,336
How are you holding up, Kara?

47
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:03,588
<i>I've got my hands full, Ma.</i>

48
00:05:03,612 --> 00:05:05,540
But these robots have convinced everyone

49
00:05:05,564 --> 00:05:06,925
that Superman's still around.

50
00:05:06,949 --> 00:05:08,659
<i>I'm so worried, dear.</i>

51
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:10,762
<i>Still no word from Clark?</i>

52
00:05:10,786 --> 00:05:13,898
No, and it's been over a month since he disappeared.

53
00:05:13,922 --> 00:05:17,852
I don't know how long I can keep this up.

54
00:05:17,876 --> 00:05:20,105
[MUTTERING IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]

55
00:05:20,129 --> 00:05:21,189
[YELLS] Hey, knock...

56
00:05:21,213 --> 00:05:22,423
it off, you greedy pig.

57
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:24,192
[GRUNTING]

58
00:05:24,216 --> 00:05:25,193
What?

59
00:05:25,217 --> 00:05:26,349
Oops.

60
00:05:29,471 --> 00:05:31,750
I mean, sorry to be a pig,

61
00:05:31,774 --> 00:05:33,974
but I've gotta eat and run.

62
00:05:36,528 --> 00:05:38,044
Weird.

63
00:05:42,434 --> 00:05:43,428
[SIGHS]

64
00:05:43,452 --> 00:05:45,796
Clark, where are you?

65
00:05:45,820 --> 00:05:47,821
♪

66
00:05:57,549 --> 00:05:59,194
Help us, please.

67
00:05:59,218 --> 00:06:01,196
[ALL MOANING]

68
00:06:01,220 --> 00:06:03,136
[GRUNTS]

69
00:06:06,041 --> 00:06:07,318
MAN: Don't leave us here.

70
00:06:07,342 --> 00:06:08,737
Who are you?

71
00:06:08,761 --> 00:06:10,288
Leave me alone.

72
00:06:10,312 --> 00:06:11,978
[ALL SCREAMING]

73
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:19,020
[GRUNTS]

74
00:06:35,170 --> 00:06:36,319
[GASPS]

75
00:06:39,925 --> 00:06:40,925
No!

76
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:49,966
The dream again?

77
00:06:52,721 --> 00:06:55,722
Maybe it's time to see Granny.

78
00:06:58,576 --> 00:06:59,576
[SHRIEKS]

79
00:07:02,231 --> 00:07:05,210
SUPERMAN: The dreams are so vivid.

80
00:07:05,234 --> 00:07:08,797
It's almost like they're symbols of something deep inside me.

81
00:07:08,821 --> 00:07:10,470
Something I've forgotten.

82
00:07:11,857 --> 00:07:13,551
There, there, my precious.

83
00:07:13,575 --> 00:07:14,952
Don't fret.

84
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:17,472
Granny's going to flush those nasty, old cobwebs

85
00:07:17,496 --> 00:07:19,474
right out of your head.

86
00:07:19,498 --> 00:07:20,892
Just relax.

87
00:07:20,916 --> 00:07:23,416
Let your mind drift back.

88
00:07:26,588 --> 00:07:28,554
[YELLING]

89
00:07:31,376 --> 00:07:32,653
♪

90
00:07:32,677 --> 00:07:34,322
GRANNY: <i>You were born on a dying world</i>

91
00:07:34,346 --> 00:07:37,742
<i>called Krypton.</i>

92
00:07:37,766 --> 00:07:39,877
<i>To save your tender, young life,</i>

93
00:07:39,901 --> 00:07:42,736
<i>your parents launched you into space.</i>

94
00:07:49,327 --> 00:07:52,979
<i>Kind fate brought you here to Apokolips,</i>

95
00:07:57,669 --> 00:08:01,816
<i>where benevolent, wise Darkseid found you.</i>

96
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:04,908
<i>He adopted you and raised you as his own.</i>

97
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:08,205
<i>He nurtured your powers</i>

98
00:08:08,229 --> 00:08:11,208
<i>and taught you of his great mission:</i>

99
00:08:11,232 --> 00:08:14,467
<i>to bring order to a lawless universe.</i>

100
00:08:18,089 --> 00:08:21,068
<i>And now, he wants you to have your own world</i>

101
00:08:21,092 --> 00:08:23,738
<i>to tame and rule.</i>

102
00:08:23,762 --> 00:08:25,294
<i>Earth.</i>

103
00:08:31,086 --> 00:08:33,097
It all seems so clear now.

104
00:08:33,121 --> 00:08:34,932
Thank you, Granny.

105
00:08:34,956 --> 00:08:38,107
That's what I'm here for, my angel.

106
00:08:42,297 --> 00:08:44,943
[CHUCKLING]

107
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:47,512
The witless fool.

108
00:08:47,536 --> 00:08:49,113
DARKSEID: Have a care, Granny.

109
00:08:49,137 --> 00:08:51,816
He must not suspect the truth too soon.

110
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:54,769
No, great Darkseid.

111
00:08:54,793 --> 00:08:57,721
The reprogramming is a complete success.

112
00:08:57,745 --> 00:08:59,958
He will attack Earth as I planned?

113
00:08:59,982 --> 00:09:04,561
Yes, uniting that planet's military force to destroy him.

114
00:09:04,585 --> 00:09:06,381
The poor lamb.

115
00:09:06,405 --> 00:09:08,900
Earth will be decimated in the battle.

116
00:09:08,924 --> 00:09:12,554
I vowed never to interfere with that world again.

117
00:09:12,578 --> 00:09:15,406
But even Highfather would not object to me restoring order

118
00:09:15,430 --> 00:09:18,498
to the confused and broken survivors.

119
00:09:20,502 --> 00:09:23,648
It's a brilliant scheme, Darkseid.

120
00:09:23,672 --> 00:09:26,839
Earth will be yours.

121
00:09:30,411 --> 00:09:32,394
♪

122
00:09:40,388 --> 00:09:41,853
[BEEPING]

123
00:09:55,753 --> 00:09:57,719
[BEEPING]

124
00:10:01,426 --> 00:10:03,487
[BEEPING LOUDER]

125
00:10:03,511 --> 00:10:04,993
[SCREAMING] I'm up, I'm up.

126
00:10:14,821 --> 00:10:17,789
Oh, great. The robot's gone haywire.

127
00:10:34,709 --> 00:10:37,838
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

128
00:10:37,862 --> 00:10:40,441
I saw it at a little gallery in the village,

129
00:10:40,465 --> 00:10:43,110
and I just had to have it.

130
00:10:43,134 --> 00:10:44,933
[SCREAMING & SHOUTING]

131
00:10:46,471 --> 00:10:48,182
I hope you saved the receipt.

132
00:10:48,206 --> 00:10:49,533
[GASPS]

133
00:10:49,557 --> 00:10:51,557
♪

134
00:10:58,498 --> 00:10:59,810
Oh, no.

135
00:10:59,834 --> 00:11:02,134
Clark will have a cow when he hears about this.

136
00:11:13,347 --> 00:11:14,787
SUPER GIRL: Oof!

137
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,484
[GRUNTING]

138
00:11:20,304 --> 00:11:21,636
Whoa!

139
00:11:26,728 --> 00:11:27,827
[GRUNTING]

140
00:11:29,831 --> 00:11:30,831
[GASPS]

141
00:11:34,051 --> 00:11:35,746
[GRUNTING]

142
00:11:35,770 --> 00:11:37,981
LEX: Super Girl.

143
00:11:38,005 --> 00:11:40,584
I should've suspected you were behind this.

144
00:11:40,608 --> 00:11:42,419
I don't know what you're talking about...

145
00:11:42,443 --> 00:11:44,755
Luthor. Lex Luthor.

146
00:11:44,779 --> 00:11:46,006
I know who you are.

147
00:11:46,030 --> 00:11:47,591
What are you trying to pull here?

148
00:11:47,615 --> 00:11:50,416
I was about to ask you the same thing.

149
00:11:52,787 --> 00:11:54,798
You see, I've known for some time now

150
00:11:54,822 --> 00:11:56,956
that<i> this</i> wasn't the genuine article.

151
00:11:59,293 --> 00:12:00,442
[METAL CLANKING]

152
00:12:02,012 --> 00:12:03,389
Is that right?

153
00:12:03,413 --> 00:12:06,326
I make it my business to know the habits of my enemies.

154
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:08,662
[BUZZING]

155
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:12,332
I can spot a fake a mile away.

156
00:12:12,356 --> 00:12:15,635
It was a simple matter to scramble this robot's circuitry

157
00:12:15,659 --> 00:12:17,421
and confirm my suspicions.

158
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:20,478
Superman is missing.

159
00:12:21,349 --> 00:12:22,614
[METAL CLANKING]

160
00:12:24,318 --> 00:12:25,713
No, he's not.

161
00:12:25,737 --> 00:12:29,288
He's just been kind of busy lately.

162
00:12:29,991 --> 00:12:31,634
It's more than that.

163
00:12:31,658 --> 00:12:34,976
I think he's gone and not coming back.

164
00:12:37,165 --> 00:12:39,393
Admit it, child.

165
00:12:39,417 --> 00:12:42,000
You can keep up this charade only so long.

166
00:12:43,237 --> 00:12:45,937
You'd be surprised at what I can do.

167
00:12:46,423 --> 00:12:48,057
[GRUNTS]

168
00:12:54,532 --> 00:12:57,577
LEX: I've always believed as you do, General Hardcastle,

169
00:12:57,601 --> 00:12:59,713
that Superman poses a threat to national,

170
00:12:59,737 --> 00:13:01,948
even global, security.

171
00:13:01,972 --> 00:13:04,968
That's why I agreed to fund this operation.

172
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:07,271
Ever since he first appeared in Metropolis,

173
00:13:07,295 --> 00:13:09,256
Project Achilles has secretly monitored

174
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,623
all his activities.

175
00:13:10,647 --> 00:13:13,643
And now, his alien friend Super Girl is using a robot

176
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:14,644
to cover for him.

177
00:13:14,668 --> 00:13:15,645
What are they up to?

178
00:13:15,669 --> 00:13:17,514
I don't know.

179
00:13:17,538 --> 00:13:20,222
But we should be on our guard.

180
00:13:30,568 --> 00:13:32,762
My troops are ready, Father.

181
00:13:32,786 --> 00:13:34,948
If you're to be a king, my son,

182
00:13:34,972 --> 00:13:37,450
you should fight under your own standard.

183
00:13:37,474 --> 00:13:39,474
♪

184
00:13:41,345 --> 00:13:43,907
I designed it myself.

185
00:13:43,931 --> 00:13:45,375
Does it displease you?

186
00:13:45,399 --> 00:13:47,744
No.

187
00:13:47,768 --> 00:13:48,967
It just seems familiar.

188
00:13:56,427 --> 00:13:58,376
I'll carry it with honor, Father.

189
00:14:10,341 --> 00:14:12,252
Onward!

190
00:14:12,276 --> 00:14:15,160
For the glory of Darkseid and Apokolips.

191
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:28,218
[BEEPING]

192
00:14:28,242 --> 00:14:29,725
Now what?

193
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:33,807
<i>Kara, have you heard the news?</i>

194
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:34,808
<i>It's too horrible.</i>

195
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:36,226
Is it about Clark?

196
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,733
<i>See for yourself, dear.</i>

197
00:14:40,204 --> 00:14:42,015
<i>The invaders came out of nowhere</i>

198
00:14:42,039 --> 00:14:44,173
<i>and struck without warning.</i>

199
00:14:46,343 --> 00:14:48,889
<i>Our forces were totally unprepared</i>

200
00:14:48,913 --> 00:14:50,796
<i>for the savage onslaught.</i>

201
00:14:54,835 --> 00:14:56,446
Let's go! Move out!

202
00:14:56,470 --> 00:14:59,149
<i>NATO's weapons, communications and defense systems</i>

203
00:14:59,173 --> 00:15:02,691
<i>were all wiped out in a matter of minutes.</i>

204
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:15,081
<i>But the biggest shock was the revelation</i>

205
00:15:15,105 --> 00:15:17,851
<i>of the invasion leader's identity.</i>

206
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:20,358
<i>Superman.</i>

207
00:15:22,546 --> 00:15:23,963
Clark.

208
00:15:36,292 --> 00:15:39,638
HARDCASTLE: Luthor, the moment we've dreaded is finally here.

209
00:15:39,662 --> 00:15:41,890
The aliens have turned against us.

210
00:15:41,914 --> 00:15:44,977
I told you they couldn't be trusted, general.

211
00:15:45,001 --> 00:15:47,412
Well, obviously that robot was just a decoy

212
00:15:47,436 --> 00:15:51,150
while he and Super Girl planned the final stages of this attack.

213
00:15:51,174 --> 00:15:52,551
Now, he's trying to knock out

214
00:15:52,575 --> 00:15:55,487
every major military system on the planet.

215
00:15:55,511 --> 00:15:57,143
There's only one thing to do.

216
00:15:58,931 --> 00:15:59,908
I'm on it.

217
00:15:59,932 --> 00:16:01,576
Keep me posted, general.

218
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:03,211
I never thought it was possible.

219
00:16:03,235 --> 00:16:04,613
Neither did I.

220
00:16:04,637 --> 00:16:06,215
The fury of these attacks.

221
00:16:06,239 --> 00:16:08,000
The cold disdain in his eyes.

222
00:16:08,024 --> 00:16:11,403
It's unlike anything I've seen before.

223
00:16:11,427 --> 00:16:14,172
MERCY: He's a completely different person.

224
00:16:14,196 --> 00:16:17,380
Soon to be a very dead one.

225
00:16:20,385 --> 00:16:23,182
I don't know what twist of fate caused this change,

226
00:16:23,206 --> 00:16:26,201
but Superman's handed us the perfect opportunity

227
00:16:26,225 --> 00:16:27,290
to destroy him.

228
00:16:29,595 --> 00:16:31,940
I intend to exploit it.

229
00:16:31,964 --> 00:16:33,947
♪

230
00:16:53,952 --> 00:16:55,712
Hit him with everything you've got.

231
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,899
I can't believe Superman's really doing this.

232
00:17:13,923 --> 00:17:14,923
Believe it.

233
00:17:21,930 --> 00:17:23,763
[SCREAMING]

234
00:17:29,105 --> 00:17:32,072
Someone's gotta talk to him, reason with him.

235
00:17:33,709 --> 00:17:35,137
Are you crazy?

236
00:17:35,161 --> 00:17:37,161
Dumb question.

237
00:17:50,742 --> 00:17:51,842
Look out!

238
00:17:53,629 --> 00:17:55,395
SUPER GIRL: That's enough, Clark.

239
00:17:58,567 --> 00:18:00,329
What do you think you're doing?

240
00:18:00,353 --> 00:18:02,269
My father's will.

241
00:18:14,199 --> 00:18:15,559
[GRUNTS] Sorry, Clark.

242
00:18:17,370 --> 00:18:18,819
But I can't let you do it.

243
00:18:31,884 --> 00:18:35,063
You wear my shield, but stand against me?

244
00:18:35,087 --> 00:18:36,870
Then die!

245
00:18:45,381 --> 00:18:47,576
What kept ya? We're running out of time.

246
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:49,916
I wanted to deliver this personally.

247
00:18:57,660 --> 00:18:58,653
Remember, general,

248
00:18:58,677 --> 00:19:00,639
you're only going to get one shot.

249
00:19:00,663 --> 00:19:02,196
Make it count.

250
00:19:09,104 --> 00:19:11,905
Superman, stop! You'll kill her.

251
00:19:12,857 --> 00:19:13,819
You?

252
00:19:13,843 --> 00:19:15,925
Yeah, it's me, Lois.

253
00:19:18,431 --> 00:19:20,609
Lois?

254
00:19:20,633 --> 00:19:23,061
You've always tried to help and protect,

255
00:19:23,085 --> 00:19:24,529
not destroy.

256
00:19:24,553 --> 00:19:25,697
What's happened to you?

257
00:19:25,721 --> 00:19:28,772
I... I don't know.

258
00:19:30,609 --> 00:19:31,724
Fire!

259
00:19:33,529 --> 00:19:34,678
Lois, get down.

260
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:39,978
Direct hit.

261
00:19:40,002 --> 00:19:41,818
No way he could've survived that.

262
00:19:45,474 --> 00:19:46,474
[COUGHS]

263
00:19:47,993 --> 00:19:50,522
[COUGHING]

264
00:19:50,546 --> 00:19:52,446
Superman?

265
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,561
Oh, my God.

266
00:19:56,585 --> 00:19:58,585
♪

267
00:20:09,613 --> 00:20:11,613
♪

